b'And if this helps at least one person look at his/her body differently, posting this (super scary) thread was worth it.'
b'But I hope this thread will serve as a good reminder to me on those days.'
b'There are still many days where I am bombarded with images of "perfect women" and struggle to love myself.'
b"My body works to keep me alive every day, and I refuse to shame my body because it doesn't meet society's standards of beauty."
b"My body will one day grow a child. My body will one day wrinkle and show all the laughing I've done."
b'I love my body AND its "flaws." My body is pretty great. Extra fat, stretch marks, acne and all.'
b'I\'m done picking apart every little detail or "imperfection" and tearing myself down.'
b"I'm not going to punish my body for not meeting somebody else's beauty standards."
b'I refuse to cover it up and feel self conscious just because somebody else may be "grossed out" by my extra fat, stretch marks, etc.'
b'My body is beautiful even though it is not "perfect". It is the only body I will ever have, and I choose to love it and take care of it.'
b'My body is beautiful even though it is riddled with stretch marks. https://t.co/ly7JuwEGfa'
b"My body is beautiful whether it's posed or natural and bloated. https://t.co/8zIphOHuMU"
b"My body is beautiful when my legs aren't shaved and when they are shaved but are covered with razor bumps. https://t.co/5b5CGSLwTt"
b'My body is beautiful even though I have extra hair on my upper lip and between my eyebrows.'
b'My body is beautiful even though I have numerous moles, blemishes, and scars. https://t.co/6SPN5RozSh'
b'My body is beautiful even though my legs squish when I sit and jiggle when I walk. https://t.co/va0gNp2owf'
b'My body is beautiful even though I have extra fat and cellulite from my ice cream and donut cravings.'
b'And sometimes that means allowing myself to eat ice cream without being overcome with guilt.'
b"I don't always make the best health choices; I do enjoy ice cream, but I still want to take care of my body."
b"I love myself and my body because it's MY body. My body is awesome! It can do so many things!!"
b"I'm done letting unrealistic expectations of beauty keep me from living my life and loving myself."
b'I grew up hating myself because my body was not society\'s version of "beautiful," but I\'m done.'
b'I have always struggled with this. No matter how many nights, months, or years I starved myself, I was always "bigger than average."'
b'Even at my lowest (almost unhealthy weight) I was wearing US size 6 or 8 (size medium) clothing.'
b'And you know what? I\'ll probably never be "skinny" in society\'s definition.'
b'I remember repeatedly asking my mom "when will I be skinny?" from as young as 9-years-old...'
b'The doctors told me I was healthy for my body type, but in society\'s eyes I\'ve always been "bigger" and it has affected me from a young age.'
b'A little bit about me. I have always been "bigger" or "big boned" as my mother always told me.'
b"I'm also all for self improvement, but better yourself because you LOVE yourself, not because you hate yourself."
b'Our bodies are beautiful no matter what society or anyone else has to say.'
b'So this is a thread to serve as a reminder to you and myself that we are beautiful.'
b"I am all for self love and body positivity, but it's hard. It's near impossible sometimes."
